ersity ba    peter j leblanc jr has lived most of his life in st louis and loves the city—its arts community its history and the people that live here   while attending washington university mr leblanc studied under muhm  reilly partner edward f reilly whom he credits for his interest in complex tax and estate planning  mr leblanc went on to work at a trust company where he advised multiple generations of families and trustees on all aspects of wealth transfer charitable gifting and tax planning at saint louis university mr leblanc received the academic achievement award for legal research and writing  he later received academic excellence awards at washington university for federal estate  gift taxation and asset protection planning prior to his career as an attorney mr leblanc worked in communications for private companies in both the manufacturing and service fields  mr leblanc views his responsibilities at muhm  reilly as a culmination of these diverse backgrounds each of which he has tailored toward serving his clients in the best possible manner  mr leblanc is a member of the missouri bar association the bar association of metropolitan st louis and the estate planning council of st louis he is admitted to practice law in missouri   contact peter j leblanc jr fidelity investments  retirement funds and online trading need help open an account open an account log out achieve more when you pay less with no annual fees and some of the most competitive prices in the industry we help your money go further find out more why invest with fidelity planning and advice from complex wealth management to your retirement needs we can help you with financial planning straightforward pricing with low minimums no annual account fees and competitive prices we can help your money go further robust investing tools get easytouse tools and the latest professional insights from our team of specialists   get your retirement score in  seconds knowing where you stand is crucial use this 